**1h fire** - good sustainable damage but low mobility\
**Wild fire staff** - same as 1h fire but different playstyle\
**Dual swords** - good burst damage and chase in 1v1\
**Carving sword** - Same as dual swords but the E reduces resistances\
**Battle axe** - good sustain and damage\
**Double bladed** - good chase and cc but needs support for the lack of damage ex: stalker jacket\
**Ava gauntlets** - good damage high mobility and has a buff purge on its E skill but very expensive compared to other weapons\
**Brawler gloves** - very good but limited to select builds\
**1h spear** - jack of all trades decent damage decent mobility and ok healing when paired with roast pork\
**Regular bow** - good in corrupted dungeons and 1v1 in general 1h dagger ** - really good with the right build with it's high burst damage\
**Bloodletter** - high mobility and has an execute for its E skill\
**Death givers** - good damage high mobility and an execute-style E skill\ **1h cursed** - damage over time and burst with it's E skill and works very well even with low ip\
**1h frost** - amazing kiting due to slow and has decent mobility with it's W skill\
**Chillhowl** - same as 1h frost in it's pros but has higher burst E and can be casted on to yourself for immunity to damage\
**1h arcane** - decent mobility decent damage and has purge on E skill\
**Blight staff** - amazing healing and great for PvE but takes skill\

**1h battleaxe** -  Scrappy melee combat with good lifesteal built in\
**1h spear** -  A more poke and kite kinda melee rather than brawling. Very satisfying\
**The entire dagger line** -  They are all very mobile and do good dmg. Some specialize in execute like blood letter or some are more burst dmg like double dagger or claws. Very fun\
**Blight staff** -  It's always good to have a healing option for when you do group content and nature staves are good weapons even solo. Can do good dmg and sustain. Plus you'll be able to heal group content.\
**Bows** -  There's a lot of good options in this. Normal bow is good single target dps. Bow of badon is a staple and good for small group content.\
**Double bladed staff** -  This one's more an honorable mention as it's kinda the meta for solo. You have so much mobility you can just kinda choose not to fight if things start going wrong.\




